description:
Penketh Support Group Lockdown and Beyond is a volunteer group set up in response to the Coronavirus Pandemic.

Since the start of lockdown we have been providing support to the elderly, vulnerable and their families in our community. Many of those we are supporting, have been asking if we are going to ‘continue our invaluable work’. So, we officially named our group ‘Penketh Support Group Lockdown and Beyond, set social media pages up and registered with Warrington Voluntary Action.

At present we are delivering supply packs, newspapers, prescriptions, shopping and other essential items to our local residents who are struggling with the restrictions of Covid-19.

We are a friendly face, someone ready to chat or an ear to listen to any anxieties they may have. Although lockdown may be easing, we are still receiving requests for help from people who still need to shield or self isolate and those affected financially due to furlough or job losses. Coronavirus is not going away anytime soon, and as a result, neither are the fears of our vulnerable and elderly, whether it be emotional or financial.


Penketh has a large elderly population and unfortunately one of the highest death rates from Covid-19 in the country, resulting in many residents feeling frightened to step out of their front door. We aim to be that friendly face, to support our vulnerable in adapting to the ‘new normal’. As the lockdown restrictions are eased, we hope to offer additional services for those who need a little extra support to re-join community activities. This will include things like: Afternoon teas, Bingo, Arts & Crafts, Gardening- all socially distanced of course. All suggestions welcome!

We are registered with Warrington Voluntary Action and have social media pages on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram. Follow our social media to see the difference our group makes and  if you need help just call, text or email us!
name: Penketh Support Group Lockdown and Beyond

description:
This volunteer service has arisen from the current COVID-19 health crisis. There is a need for some members of the community who may need to self-isolate to receive help from others, be it in the form of help with shopping, IT support, posting letters and/or packages, or needing someone to talk to.

Equally, there's a requirement for a recipient of any help to know that any volunteer is bona fide. Hence all volunteers have to be recommended by another member of the community, given that news articles are already circulating of thieves and scammers presenting themselves as volunteers elsewhere in the country.

The purpose of this service is to provide a single view of community members known to need help and set them in contact with those able to provide that help, so that volunteering is not done in a piecemeal, sporadic fashion wherein some people may fall through the cracks, but is instead done consistently. You are able to pick any of the following support services.

Community Collection Services: Volunteers collect shopping, medication or other essential supplies for you who are self-isolating, and delivering these supplies to your home.

Check-in and Chat Services: Volunteers provide short-term telephone support to you who are at risk of loneliness as a consequence of self-isolation.

Community First Aid: Volunteers are individual who has undertaken appropriate training . They must hold a valid certificate of competence in either: first aid at work, emergency first aid at work or any other level of training or qualification that is appropriate.
